Ad Text:
Job Type: Contract (6 months likely extension)

Salary: 750 per day

We are seeking an experienced Data Solution Designer to lead our modern data platform, manage high-performing teams, and drive end-to-end delivery of enterprise analytics solutions. You will define strategy, implement scalable cloud-native data platforms, and partner with business & product teams to enable data-driven decision making.

Key Responsibilities

Define and deliver the enterprise Data & Analytics strategy, quarterly roadmaps, and long-term platform vision.
Lead and mentor Analytics Engineers, Data Engineers, BI Developers and Analysts.
Partner with Product, Marketing, Finance, and Tech teams to align data priorities.
Drive governance, data quality, security, platform lifecycle management and FinOps optimisation.
Own architecture & operations of Snowflake/GCP/AWS analytics platforms.
Oversee ingestion pipelines, ELT/ETL development, modelling and analytics layer design.
Implement DataOps, MLOps and Infrastructure-as-Code practices (Terraform).
Ensure reliability, scalability, cost-efficiency of the full data stack.

Key Skills & Experience

Snowflake, BigQuery or AWS data platforms
dbt (Core/Cloud), Fivetran, Segment
Data Lake architecture (S3/GCS/ADLS)
Streaming (Kafka, Pub/Sub)
Terraform / IaC / GitOps
Data modelling (star, vault, semantic models)
Looker, Tableau or equivalent
Experience enabling Data Science teams (Feature Stores, ML pipelines)

Location: Sydney (Hybrid)

Type: Contract (6 months with potential extension)

We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Engineer to design, develop, and optimise data pipelines and cloud-based platform components within a modern data ecosystem. This position blends hands-on technical delivery with leadership across data projects, enabling scalable and reusable data assets to support analytics, insights, and operational use cases.

As a senior member of the Data Platform Engineering team, you'll help shape engineering standards, mentor junior engineers, and work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure solutions are high quality, performant, and production-ready.

Key Responsibilities

Design, build, and maintain reliable and efficient data pipelines using AWS services (Glue, Lambda, S3) and Snowflake
Translate solution and modelling specifications into robust technical implementations
Participate in design discussions, peer reviews, and contribute to code quality improvements
Implement logging, monitoring, and error-handling features across all data pipelines
Apply CI/CD best practices and collaborate with DevOps to automate build, test, and deployment workflows
Develop solutions with scalability and reusability in mind
Mentor junior engineers and contribute to documentation and team knowledge sharing
Work with Data Ops teams to optimise performance and ensure deployment readiness
Partner with Solution Designers and Data Modellers to deliver fit-for-purpose data assets
Act as a technical liaison between engineering teams and broader project stakeholders

Collaboration

You'll work closely with:

Solution Designers and Data Modellers to ensure alignment between design and delivery
DevOps Engineers to implement CI/CD and deployment pipelines
Data Ops and Test Engineers to support monitoring, troubleshooting, and validation processes
Technical Leads and Managers to deliver scalable and maintainable data solutions

Qualifications & Experience

Essential:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Data Engineering, or related field
Strong SQL and Python skills
Experience with data pipeline orchestration, transformation, and cloud-native tools (Snowflake, AWS Glue, Lambda, S3)
Familiarity with CI/CD and version control practices
5+ years' experience in data engineering or related development roles
Proven ability to deliver end-to-end data solutions in cloud environments
Demonstrated leadership across data delivery workstreams

Desirable:

Snowflake and/or AWS certifications
Exposure to data quality frameworks or tools such as dbt or Great Expectations
Experience building modular and reusable data frameworks
Background in public sector, insurance, or regulated industries
Familiarity with real-time or machine learning data workflows
Experience working within Agile delivery environments

We’re looking for a talented and driven Embedded Software Engineer to help build, scale, and support complex sensor systems operating in real-world environments. In this role, you’ll design and implement embedded software that runs on Linux-based systems, contributing to projects that push the boundaries of real-time data processing, RF signal detection, and automated response.
  
You’ll work closely with teams spanning AI/ML, data science, hardware engineering, and cloud infrastructure to create robust solutions capable of handling mission-critical workloads. The software you build will directly support applications in security, defence, and remote surveillance.

What You’ll Be Doing

Develop and maintain embedded software features on Linux-based edge systems
Collaborate across disciplines to meet operational and performance requirements
Ensure code is designed for resource-constrained, high-uptime environments
Implement features using modern C++ and Python, depending on project needs
Participate in software design discussions, code reviews, and performance tuning
Work on inter-process communication mechanisms for modular, scalable architectures
Create and maintain high-quality technical documentation for implemented components
Contribute to the continuous integration pipeline and system testing frameworks
Support system monitoring, logging, and observability in production deployments
Engage with DevOps and infrastructure specialists to improve deployment workflows
Your Background

Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related technical field
Proven experience developing applications in modern C++ 
Strong understanding of Linux development (embedded Linux preferred)
Familiarity with multi-process systems and IPC mechanisms
Exposure to Docker, Git, CI/CD pipelines (e.g., GitLab), and versioning tools
Experience with design patterns, testing, and scalable software architecture
Bonus Points For

Knowledge of concurrency, performance optimisation, or low-latency systems
Hands-on experience with Go programming
Background in machine learning, RF signal processing, or DSP
Exposure to FPGA, sensor integration, or systems running in remote deployments
Understanding of DevOps practices, including observability and automated deployments
Interested candidates should click Apply and send through their details, or you can email me at farid@thedrivegroup.com.au for more info or call me on 0435777965!

We’re on the lookout for a number of Embedded Systems Engineers to join a product development team in Sydney. Reporting to the Systems Engineering Manager, these roles offer the opportunity to make a direct impact in a niche, fast-growing defence technology sector.
  
You’ll be at the heart of developing current and next-generation products, bridging the gap between stakeholder needs and engineering outcomes. This means gathering, analysing, and managing requirements, ensuring complex systems come together seamlessly, and empowering development teams to work towards common goals. If you thrive on autonomy, responsibility, and collaboration, this role is for you.
  
What you’ll do

Work with a team of systems engineers across sensors & effectors and product development to define and deliver new capabilities.
Develop and embed systems engineering processes that promote best practice, efficiency, and quality.
Manage documentation of system design, requirements, and test strategies, with a strong focus on integration testing.
Act as the bridge between stakeholders and engineering teams, communicating risks, issues, and progress.
Own technical problems, coordinate cross-functional solutions, and drive continual product improvement.
Partner with Product and Project Management to align deliverables and milestones.
Bring the customer’s voice into development teams, ensuring new features meet real-world needs.
What you’ll bring

Bachelor’s or Master’s in Systems, Mechatronics, Electrical, Mechanical, Computer Science, or similar.
3+ years’ experience in systems engineering within complex product development.
Strong grasp of systems engineering frameworks, tools, and lifecycle principles.
Experience with requirements management for hardware/software systems.
Ability to work independently and collaboratively, taking ownership of deliverables.
Desirable: experience with AI-enabled systems, RF hardware/software, electronic warfare, or distributed systems.
Bonus: exposure to cybersecurity in systems engineering, Atlassian tools (Jira/Confluence).
A drive to excel in a high-empowerment, fast-paced, mission-driven environment.
Bonus Points For

Exposure to electronic warfare, artificial intelligence, or machine learning domains.
Experience conducting product demonstrations, gathering end-user feedback, or supporting external product events.
This is a fantastic opportunity for systems-minded engineers ready to take on a diverse, high-impact role within a company at the forefront of counter-threat and autonomous system technologies.

For more info you can contact me at farid@thedrivegroup.com.au or click Apply and send through your details and I'll be in touch!

We’re looking for a Senior Infrastructure Engineer with extensive experience running Kubernetes at scale to join the team as they build out a market-first K8s cluster running on top of globally distributed data centers. 

This rapidly growing organization is at the forefront of developing technologies to counter the increasing use of drones for nefarious purposes, including battlefield scenarios, terrorism, contraband delivery, and commercial espionage. The company is poised for significant growth in the coming years with a substantial team based in their Sydney headquarters and a global presence in the USA, Europe, and the Middle East.

Deep knowledge of K8’s on bare-metal Linux is essential for this role, as they operate at the cutting edge of high-performance infrastructure at petabyte+ scale. Key responsibilities on top of this include addressing high-volume data processing, enabling MLOps projects (ClearML), and integrating machine learning services. This role reports to the Director of Infrastructure.
   
Responsibilities, Duties and Expectations 

Lead the architecture and ownership of the K8’s cluster (multiple remote nodes) 
Work with the team on building and improving the Ops infrastructure  
Collaborate with software and technology teams to solve complex problems involving distributed systems, data engineering, security, and system resilience
Find solutions for both on-prem and cloud-based systems
Qualifications, Experience and Skills 

Extensive knowledge of Kubernetes, and the ability to use K8’s on Linux - CKA/CKS 
Advanced knowledge of Linux, specifically Layer 1 and Layer 2 networking, Process Monitoring, Networks, System Performance, and Bash Scripting
Experience working in MLOps – ClearML, Kubeflow etc
Experience with Terraform and Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
Expertise in configuration management tools such as Ansible, Puppet, or Chef
Strong experience with AWS
Solid understanding of networking and security
Interested candidates are encouraged to apply promptly. Or you can email me at farid@thedrivegroup.com.au for more details.

A global leader in defence technology is seeking an Algorithms Team Lead to head its core algorithms group in Sydney. This team develops the intelligence behind advanced detection and electronic warfare systems, digital signal processing, and software engineering to deliver breakthrough performance in real-world environments.
  
Reporting to senior engineering leadership, this position is equal parts technical strategy, people leadership, and execution. The successful candidate will define the vision for algorithmic innovation, drive delivery across complex projects, and mentor a high-performing team of engineers and scientists.
  
Key Responsibilities

Lead and grow a multidisciplinary team spanning DSP and software engineering.
Define technical direction and execution plans for algorithm research, development, and deployment.
Bridge business priorities with engineering outcomes, ensuring innovation delivers measurable value.
Oversee project delivery — setting milestones, managing dependencies, and ensuring successful execution.
Champion best practices in algorithm design, experimentation, and software engineering.
Oversee testing and validation of algorithmic solutions across multiple products and use cases.
Collaborate with other technical leaders to align strategies across sensors, effectors, and systems.
Provide ongoing mentorship, technical guidance, and career development for team members.  
Skills & Experience

Bachelor’s or higher degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, or related field.
Minimum 3 years’ experience leading engineering or research teams.
At least 3 years’ experience working with AI/ML-based or data-driven systems.
Strong proficiency in Python and C/C++.
Experience with project management tools such as Jira and Confluence.
Proven ability to translate technical objectives into business outcomes.
Skilled communicator who can work effectively with multidisciplinary engineering teams.
Track record of delivering commercial, production-ready solutions end-to-end.
Background in Electronic Warfare (EW), Radio Frequency (RF), or advanced sensing technologies is highly valued.  
Ideal Candidate
  
You’re an engineering leader who thrives on solving complex technical problems and bringing ideas to life through collaboration. You stay ahead of emerging trends in AI and signal processing, and you know how to turn theory into deployed capability. You lead by example, mentor others, and take pride in building systems that make a tangible difference.
  
For more info, you can either apply here, or contact me on 0435777965 or farid@thedrivegroup.com.au

Position Description:


Recognised as one of the world’s largest IT and business consulting firms, CGI has offices across Australia, supporting local public and private sector clients to solve real business problems.

We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer who will focuse on developing robust solutions for data ingestion, transformation, and optimization while ensuring performance, governance, and long-term sustainability. You’ll act as a technical lead, collaborating across teams to deliver high-quality data capabilities that empower analytics and business intelligence across the organization.

Flexible work is available including hybrid work from client’s site at Port Melbourne

Your future duties and responsibilities:


• Lead the design, development, and continuous improvement of data pipelines, frameworks, and architecture that support complex transformation and modelling requirements.
• Define, document, and maintain data processing logic, ensuring clarity across requirements, solutions, reconciliation steps, and ETL/ELT processes.
• Translate business needs into practical, scalable data models and engineering solutions that can be reused across multiple systems and domains.
• Partner with other engineers and cross-functional teams to guide the creation of data solutions, ensuring consistency, scalability, and security.
• Support project execution through regular progress updates, issue tracking, and risk management reporting.
• Identify and recommend improvements to existing data platforms, leveraging emerging cloud features and capabilities.
• Work closely with architecture and engineering teams to optimise performance, availability, and cost across Azure environments.
• Maintain and refine data quality and governance frameworks to uphold integrity and compliance across all data products.
• Foster strong communication channels with stakeholders, ensuring transparency, collaboration, and mutual understanding of project goals.
• Provide technical leadership, mentorship, and guidance to data engineers, promoting best practices in design, development, and delivery.
• Collaborate with project managers and senior stakeholders to prioritise workloads and align technical deliverables with strategic objectives.
• Build trusted relationships across teams by proactively communicating updates, challenges, and improvement opportunities.

Required qualifications to be successful in this role:


• Strong technical foundation with a solid understanding of database concepts, along with hands-on experience using data development tools (ETL frameworks) and programming languages such as SQL and Python to design, build, and document data extraction, transformation, and loading processes.
• Demonstrated ability to analyse business operations in depth, translate requirements into actionable solutions, and design and implement tools that address specific business needs while continuously building on existing knowledge.
• Proficiency with several of the following technologies and programming tools:
o Azure Data Lake
o Azure Data Factory
o Azure Databricks (including SQL and Python)
o Azure SQL Server
o Azure DevOps / Git
• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the capability to clearly explain technical information and data concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.
• A creative problem-solver with the confidence to design innovative solutions where standard approaches or precedents may not exist.
• A proactive approach to learning and professional growth — keen to experiment with new ideas, share insights, and support the development of others within the team.

Skills:

Azure Data Factory
Azure Data Lake
Azure DevOps
Python
What you can expect from us:


Together, as owners, let’s turn meaningful insights into action.

Life at CGI is rooted in ownership, teamwork, respect and belonging. Here, you’ll reach your full potential because…

You are invited to be an owner from day 1 as we work together to bring our Dream to life. That’s why we call ourselves CGI Partners rather than employees. We benefit from our collective success and actively shape our company’s strategy and direction.

Your work creates value. You’ll develop innovative solutions and build relationships with teammates and clients while accessing global capabilities to scale your ideas, embrace new opportunities, and benefit from expansive industry and technology expertise.

You’ll shape your career by joining a company built to grow and last. You’ll be supported by leaders who care about your health and well-being and provide you with opportunities to deepen your skills and broaden your horizons.

Come join our team—one of the largest IT and business consulting services firms in the world.

Position Description:


Recognised as one of the world’s largest IT and business consulting firms, CGI has offices across Australia, supporting local public and private sector clients to solve real business problems.

We are looking for a Data Engineer who will play a vital role in transforming business needs into practical data-driven solutions. You’ll be responsible for collecting, preparing, and optimizing data through modelling, transformation, and integration activities.

Flexible work is available including hybrid work from client’s site at Port Melbourne

Your future duties and responsibilities:


• Take ownership of data design and delivery — ensuring the accuracy, reliability, and security of data managed across various platforms.

• Contribute to the analysis, design, and build of repeatable frameworks for data ingestion, transformation, migration, and integration

• Develop, test, and maintain ETL processes and data pipelines that support ongoing and future business requirements.

• Produce and maintain documentation that captures data flows, transformation logic, and underlying requirements in line with agreed organisational standards.

• Translate business data requirements into effective, scalable technical solutions that can be adopted throughout the organisation.

• Collaborate with senior engineers, architects, and delivery teams to plan workloads, estimate effort, and deliver solutions that meet performance and design expectations.

• Support project reporting by sharing progress updates, highlighting potential risks or issues, and responding to information requests from project leadership.

• Apply and uphold established Data Quality and Data Governance standards, ensuring that all solutions meet compliance, accuracy, and reliability benchmarks.

• Maintain open and transparent communication with stakeholders, promoting collaboration, trust, and alignment throughout delivery cycles.

Required qualifications to be successful in this role:


• Solid technical understanding of database design and operation, along with practical experience using ETL tools and programming languages such as SQL and Python to extract, transform, and load data efficiently.

• Ability to analyse and interpret business processes, translating them into technical specifications and robust data solutions.

• Experience working with several of the following platforms and technologies:
o Azure Data Lake
o Azure Data Factory
o Azure Databricks (including SQL and Python)
o Azure SQL Server
o Azure DevOps / Git

• Strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the capability to explain technical details clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.
• A collaborative and curious mindset — eager to learn new technologies, share insights, and continuously improve existing solutions.
• Creative and analytical problem-solving ability, with a focus on designing innovative, fit-for-purpose data solutions.

Skills:

Analytical Thinking
Data Quality Management
What you can expect from us:


Together, as owners, let’s turn meaningful insights into action.

Life at CGI is rooted in ownership, teamwork, respect and belonging. Here, you’ll reach your full potential because…

You are invited to be an owner from day 1 as we work together to bring our Dream to life. That’s why we call ourselves CGI Partners rather than employees. We benefit from our collective success and actively shape our company’s strategy and direction.

Your work creates value. You’ll develop innovative solutions and build relationships with teammates and clients while accessing global capabilities to scale your ideas, embrace new opportunities, and benefit from expansive industry and technology expertise.

You’ll shape your career by joining a company built to grow and last. You’ll be supported by leaders who care about your health and well-being and provide you with opportunities to deepen your skills and broaden your horizons.

Come join our team—one of the largest IT and business consulting services firms in the world.

Applicants to this role must have work authorization in Australia as this role is not eligible for work visa sponsorship.

Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience.
2 years of experience with software development in one or more programming languages, or 1 year of experience with an advanced degree in an industry setting.
Preferred qualifications:

Master's degree or PhD in Computer Science, or a related technical field.
2 years of experience with Java/C++, performance, large-scale systems data analysis, visualization tools or debugging.
2 years of experience with data structures or algorithms in either an academic or industry setting.
Experience in code and system health, diagnosis and resolution, and software test engineering.
Experience developing accessible technologies.

About the job
Google's software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how billions of users connect, explore, and interact with information and one another. Our products need to handle information at massive scale, and extend well beyond web search. We're looking for engineers who bring fresh ideas from all areas, including information retrieval, distributed computing, large-scale system design, networking and data storage, security, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, UI design and mobile; the list goes on and is growing every day. As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.Google Photos is a photo sharing and storage service developed by Google. Photos is one of the most sought after products at Google and is looking for both client-side (web and mobile), with server-side (search, storage, serving) and machine intelligence (learning, computer vision) Software Engineers. We are dedicated to making Google experiences centered around the user.

Responsibilities

Write product or system development code.
Participate in, or lead design reviews with peers and stakeholders to decide among available technologies.
Review code developed by other developers and provide feedback to ensure best practices (e.g., style guidelines, checking code in, accuracy, testability, and efficiency).
Contribute to existing documentation or educational content and adapt content based on product/program updates and user feedback.
Triage product or system issues and debug/track/resolve by analyzing the sources of issues and the impact on hardware, network, or service operations and quality.
